docs: This is the contract constructor, called only once when the contract is deployed.
The number of nodes that will run with the contract stake, as configured by the owner.
endpoints.name: getNumNodes

docs: Each node gets a node id. This is in order to be able to iterate over their data.
This is a mapping from node BLS key to node id.
The key is the bytes "node_id" concatenated with the BLS key. The value is the node id.
Ids start from 1 because 0 means unset of None.
endpoints.name: getNodeId

docs: Each delegator gets a user id. This is in order to be able to iterate over their data.
This is a mapping from delegator address to delegator id.
The key is the bytes "user_id" concatenated with their public key.
The value is the user id.
endpoints.name: getUserId

docs: Retrieves the number of delegators, including the owner,
even if they no longer have anything in the contract.
endpoints.name: getNumUsers

docs: Yields how much a user has staked in the contract.
endpoints.name: getUserStake

docs: Owner activates specific nodes.
endpoints.name: stakeNodes

docs: Unstakes from the auction smart contract.
The nodes will stop receiving rewards, but stake cannot be yet reclaimed.
This operation is performed by the owner.
Does not unstake tokens.
endpoints.name: unStakeNodes

docs: Unstakes from the auction smart contract.
The nodes will stop receiving rewards, but stake cannot be yet reclaimed.
This operation is performed by the owner.
Also unstakes tokens.
endpoints.name: unStakeNodesAndTokens

docs: Owner can retry a callback in case of callback failure.
Warning: misuse can lead to state inconsistency.
endpoints.name: forceNodeUnBondPeriod

docs: Calls unbond for all provided nodes. Will fail if node cannot be unbonded.
endpoints.name: unBondNodes

docs: Calls unbond for all nodes that are in the unbond period and are due.
Nothing happens if no nodes can be unbonded.
endpoints.name: unBondAllPossibleNodes

docs: Claims from auction SC funds that were sent but are not required to run the nodes.
endpoints.name: claimUnusedFunds

docs: Yields the address of the contract with which staking will be performed.
This address is standard in the protocol, but it is saved in storage to avoid hardcoding it.
endpoints.name: getAuctionContractAddress

docs: The proportion of rewards that goes to the owner as compensation for running the nodes.
endpoints.name: getServiceFee

docs: The minimum proportion of stake that has to be provided by the owner.
endpoints.name: getOwnerMinStakeShare

docs: Minimum number of n_blocks between unstake and fund getting into inactive state.
endpoints.name: getNumBlocksBeforeUnBond

docs: Delegators are not allowed make transactions with less then this amount of stake (of any type).
Zero means disabled.
endpoints.name: getMinimumStake

docs: Yields all the rewards received by the contract since its creation.
This value is monotonously increasing - it can never decrease.
Handing out rewards will not decrease this value.
This is to keep track of how many funds entered the contract. It ignores any funds leaving the contract.
Individual rewards are computed based on this value.
For each user we keep a record on what was the value of the historical rewards when they last claimed.
Subtracting that from the current historical rewards yields how much accumulated in the contract since they last claimed.
endpoints.name: getTotalCumulatedRewards

docs: Yields how much a user is able to claim in rewards at the present time.
Does not update storage.
endpoints.name: getClaimableRewards

docs: Utility readonly function to check how many unclaimed rewards currently reside in the contract.
endpoints.name: getTotalUnclaimedRewards

docs: Invariant: should never return error.
endpoints.name: validateOwnerStakeShare

docs: Invariant: should never return error.
endpoints.name: validateDelegationCapInvariant

docs: Continues executing any interrupted operation.
Returns true if still out of gas, false if computation completed.
endpoints.name: continueGlobalOperation

docs: Total delegation cap can be modified by owner only.
It will recalculate and set the checkpoint for all the delegators
endpoints.name: modifyTotalDelegationCap

docs: The stake per node can be changed by the owner.
It does not get set in the constructor, so the owner has to manually set it after the contract is deployed.
endpoints.name: setServiceFee

docs: Retrieve those rewards to which the caller is entitled.
Will send:
- new rewards
- rewards that were previously computed but not sent
endpoints.name: claimRewards

docs: Delegate stake to the smart contract.
Stake is initially inactive, so does it not produce rewards.
endpoints.name: stake

docs: unStake - the user will announce that he wants to get out of the contract
selected funds will change from active to inactive, but claimable only after unBond period ends
endpoints.name: unStake

docs: Raw id of the last checkpoint reached by any of the dust cleanup endpoints.
endpoints.name: dustCleanupCheckpoint

docs: Counts fund buckets in the waiting list that are below a certain threshold.
Unlike most views, yields the number of entries, rather than the sum of EGLD.
endpoints.name: countDustItemsWaitingList

docs: Counts fund buckets in the active staking list that are below a certain threshold.
Unlike most views, yields the number of entries, rather than the sum of EGLD.
endpoints.name: countDustItemsActive

docs: Unstakes all fund buckets in the waiting list that are below a certain threshold.
Will stop if running low on gas.
Does not block the rest of the contract. If any operation interferes with an interrupted
dust cleanup, the operation can be begun again.
It will auto-reset if the list ends or the current item is no longer valid.
endpoints.name: dustCleanupWaitingList

docs: Unstakes and unbonds all active fund buckets that are below a certain threshold.
Unlike the regular unstake/unbond process, it will send the funds directly in `WithdrawOnly` state.
Will stop if running low on gas.
Does not block the rest of the contract. If any operation interferes with an interrupted
dust cleanup, the operation can be begun again.
It will auto-reset if the list ends or the current item is no longer valid.
endpoints.name: dustCleanupActive

docs: Models the interrupted state of compute_all_rewards.
Funds that can only be extracted from contract. Will never be used as stake.
variants.name: WithdrawOnly

docs: Inactive stake, waiting in the queue to be activated.
variants.name: Waiting

docs: Stake is locked in the protocol and rewards are coming in.
Users cannot withdraw stake, but they can exchange their share of the total stake amongst each other.
variants.name: Active

docs: Same as Active, but no rewards are coming in.
variants.name: UnStaked

docs: A unit of balance, usually stake.
Contains a description of the source/intent of the funds, together with a balance.
Models any computation that can pause itself when it runs out of gas and continue in another block.
Models the steps that need to be executed when modifying the total delegation cap.
Contains data needed to be persisted while performing a change in the total delegation cap.
Status of a node.
Node is registered in delegation, but not in the auction SC.
variants.name: Inactive

docs: Stake call to auction sent, but callback not yet received.
variants.name: PendingActivation

docs: Node stake was sent to the auction SC, but the transaction failed for the node.
No longer used.
variants.name: ActivationFailed

docs: Node is registered in the auction SC, active and producing rewards.
variants.name: Active

docs: UnStake call to auction sent, but callback not yet received.
variants.name: PendingDeactivation

docs: Same as Active, but no rewards are coming in.
This is necessary for a period of time before the stake can be retrieved and unlocked.
variants.name: UnBondPeriod

docs: UnBond call to auction sent, but callback not yet received.
`unbond_started` field is needed in case unbonding fails and the UnBondPeriod state needs to be restored.
variants.name: PendingUnBond

docs: Node completely removed from the delegation contract.
variants.name: Removed

docs: indicates that operation was completed
variants.name: completed

docs: indicates that operation was interrupted prematurely, due to low gas
variants.name: interrupted
